<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}+{8}{y}={8}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{6}{x}-{6}{y}=-{6}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8"/></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({2},{3}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}+{8}{y}={8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}={8}-{\left({8}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{8}-{\left({8}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{8}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{\left(\frac{{{8}-{\left({8}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{8}}}}\right)}+-{6}{y}=-{6}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{6}}{{-{{8}}}}\cdot{\left({8}\right)}-\frac{{6}}{{-{{8}}}}{\left({8}\right)}{y}+-{6}{y}=-{6}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}-{\left({6}\right)}{y}+-{6}{y}=-{6}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{y}+{\left(-{6}\right)}{y}=-{6}--{6}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{y}+{\left(-{6}\right)}{y}={0}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({6}+{\left(-{6}\right)}\right)}{y}={0}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0}{y}={0}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{0}}{{0}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={3}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}+{8}{\left({3}\right)}={8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}+{\left({24}\right)}={8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}={8}-{\left({24}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}=-{16}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{16}}{{-{{8}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={2}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({2},{3}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>